The paper proposes a state estimator algorithm for power systems, which involves distributed computation and real-time processing of measurements. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the use of the belief propagation algorithm and numerical simulations indicate that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. The focus on power systems and the use of the DC model suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper's title explicitly mentions state estimation, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
